'''Sigurd Lersbryggen''' (born [[8 July]] [[1901]] in [[Str<U+00F8>mm]], died [[2 February]] [[1980]]) is a Norwegian politician for the [[Conservative Party of Norway|Conservative Party]].

He was elected to the [[Stortinget|Norwegian Parliament]] from [[Vestfold]] in 1945, and was re-elected on two occasions.

Lersbryggen served as mayor of [[Str<U+00F8>mm]] municipality in the periods 1934&ndash;1937, 1937&ndash;1940 and 1945, and as a regular municipality council member in 1931&ndash;1934, 1940&ndash;1941 and 1955&ndash;1959.

